WEBVTT

00:00:10.225 --> 00:00:10.865
What?

00:00:12.265 --> 00:00:13.174
The deputy had an accident?

00:00:14.745 --> 00:00:16.851
The assailant killed in the
shootout was indeed one of Burin’s men.

00:00:16.916 --> 00:00:18.048
It's a good thing Vicky is in there,

00:00:18.807 --> 00:00:19.897
otherwise I'd be worried.

00:00:20.072 --> 00:00:21.467
Not only are you a great driver,

00:00:21.811 --> 00:00:23.787
but you also have such strong determination.

00:00:25.505 --> 00:00:27.192
I'm so proud of you.

00:00:27.823 --> 00:00:30.327
My son just came back
from abroad earlier this year.

00:00:30.466 --> 00:00:32.801
I'd like him to get to know your daughter.

00:00:34.013 --> 00:00:35.417
If the two of them like each other.

00:00:35.790 --> 00:00:36.724
That would be wonderful.

00:00:37.580 --> 00:00:39.977
I never interfere in my child's private life.

00:01:21.862 --> 00:01:22.297
Uh...

00:01:22.756 --> 00:01:25.115
Congratulations on the top score.

00:01:25.731 --> 00:01:27.456
You certainly lived up to
your reputation, Captain Tara.

00:01:29.835 --> 00:01:30.688
How did you know?

00:01:30.759 --> 00:01:31.343
Well

00:01:31.465 --> 00:01:33.272
I'm your fan-club.

00:01:33.823 --> 00:01:34.303
Hey.

00:01:34.807 --> 00:01:38.267
I saw the news of Captain Tara's raid
at Pak Khlong.

00:01:38.493 --> 00:01:40.199
- It was so cool.
- Really?

00:01:40.416 --> 00:01:41.610
It was so cool.

00:01:41.965 --> 00:01:42.940
- And then...
- 021

00:01:44.306 --> 00:01:45.091
What are you doing here alone?

00:01:45.882 --> 00:01:47.076
Why aren't you talking to the others, huh?

00:01:47.865 --> 00:01:49.734
We're allowed to use our
real names and swap contacts now

00:01:53.983 --> 00:01:54.860
Probably...

00:01:55.213 --> 00:01:56.712
Nobody wants to get to know me.

00:01:58.270 --> 00:01:59.592
I’m sorry for making you feel bad.

00:02:00.451 --> 00:02:01.506
That was my mistake.

00:02:03.073 --> 00:02:04.478
It’s totally fine.

00:02:05.595 --> 00:02:06.265
Well,

00:02:06.507 --> 00:02:07.248
you can’t

00:02:07.847 --> 00:02:09.393
please everyone all the time.

00:02:10.025 --> 00:02:11.589
There are bound to be things we don't like.

00:02:11.722 --> 00:02:12.297
Hmm.

00:02:13.198 --> 00:02:14.905
Your mindset has improved a lot.

00:02:15.939 --> 00:02:18.125
But honestly, during
the training, I secretly admired you.

00:02:20.825 --> 00:02:21.233
Wait,

00:02:22.078 --> 00:02:23.162
What were you admiring?

00:02:23.779 --> 00:02:24.596
Oh.

00:02:25.201 --> 00:02:26.001
you criticized me so hard.

00:02:26.967 --> 00:02:28.537
I wanted to run home on the very first day.

00:02:30.232 --> 00:02:31.764
But you made it through everything,
didn't you?

00:02:33.305 --> 00:02:34.125
You did a great job.

00:03:09.115 --> 00:03:09.924
Yay!

00:03:19.853 --> 00:03:21.210
It’s because I’ve had great encouragement.

00:03:21.515 --> 00:03:22.739
That’s how I’ve made it this far.

00:03:26.321 --> 00:03:28.158
And thank you for being so tough on me,
Instructor.

00:03:29.079 --> 00:03:30.362
For making me realize that

00:03:31.616 --> 00:03:32.715
I am...

00:03:35.275 --> 00:03:36.507
Stronger than I ever thought I could be.

00:03:44.727 --> 00:03:45.390
Cheers!

00:03:46.825 --> 00:03:47.222
Cheers.

00:03:49.183 --> 00:03:49.761
Uh-huh.

00:03:50.756 --> 00:03:51.239
Hey.

00:03:52.436 --> 00:03:54.048
Drinking like that will knock you out.

00:03:55.565 --> 00:03:56.564
Hmm.

00:03:57.521 --> 00:03:58.576
In other matters,

00:03:59.044 --> 00:04:00.730
I might not be able to compete with anyone.

00:04:01.225 --> 00:04:02.155
But when it comes to drinking,

00:04:02.851 --> 00:04:03.933
I'm the most confident.

00:04:04.925 --> 00:04:05.633
Cheers!

00:04:05.835 --> 00:04:06.650
Bottoms up.

00:04:19.070 --> 00:04:20.762
It’s already going to my head tonight.

00:04:25.909 --> 00:04:27.316
That's not called being confident.

00:04:27.936 --> 00:04:29.162
That's called being cocky.

00:04:29.888 --> 00:04:30.579
Huh?

00:04:32.339 --> 00:04:33.965
Then why didn't you stop me?

00:04:34.916 --> 00:04:35.956
You were too busy talking."

00:04:37.524 --> 00:04:38.916
So, you're not just cocky.

00:04:39.705 --> 00:04:40.973
But you also like playing the victim.

00:04:45.705 --> 00:04:46.756
Hey, careful.

00:05:13.773 --> 00:05:15.530
See? Always playing the victim like this.

00:05:21.382 --> 00:05:21.912
Foul

00:05:22.724 --> 00:05:23.467
mouth.

00:05:36.057 --> 00:05:37.242
But you're also cute.

00:05:47.512 --> 00:05:48.004
Hey,

00:05:48.410 --> 00:05:49.521
you're talking nonsense because you're drunk.

00:05:51.512 --> 00:05:52.475
It's time for you to go to bed.

00:05:53.793 --> 00:05:54.374
Go on.

00:05:58.425 --> 00:06:00.318
I don't want to go back yet

00:06:13.278 --> 00:06:14.173
Can we go to the beach?

00:06:24.336 --> 00:06:25.745
Please.

00:06:26.785 --> 00:06:29.429
We're leaving soon,
and haven't even gone for a swim yet.

00:06:31.559 --> 00:06:32.309
Please.

00:06:32.540 --> 00:06:33.417
Please. Please.

00:06:34.199 --> 00:06:34.712
Please.

00:06:34.863 --> 00:06:35.269
Please.

00:06:36.093 --> 00:06:36.590
Umm.

00:06:37.977 --> 00:06:38.700
Ok.

00:06:41.239 --> 00:06:41.690
Go.

00:06:46.866 --> 00:06:47.598
Hey.

00:06:47.749 --> 00:06:48.339
You.

00:06:48.786 --> 00:06:49.411
You.

00:06:50.448 --> 00:06:51.393
Wait.

00:06:51.636 --> 00:06:52.430
Wait.

00:06:52.810 --> 00:06:54.291
We're here.

00:07:05.947 --> 00:07:06.540
Hey.

00:07:07.497 --> 00:07:09.346
The instructor said
we can use our real names now.

00:07:11.088 --> 00:07:13.370
You’ve known my name since
the day I ordered that cake.

00:07:14.330 --> 00:07:15.263
Umm.

00:07:16.093 --> 00:07:17.867
But I haven't told you my name yet.

00:07:19.275 --> 00:07:20.312
So tell me then.

00:07:21.379 --> 00:07:22.964
But if you don't want to know,

00:07:23.630 --> 00:07:24.647
I don't have to tell you.

00:07:27.337 --> 00:07:28.386
Of course I want to know.

00:07:29.118 --> 00:07:30.173
Come on, tell me already.

00:07:32.442 --> 00:07:33.379
I'm Vicky.

00:07:34.016 --> 00:07:35.423
My real name is Phavika.

00:07:38.848 --> 00:07:40.022
That's a very beautiful name.

00:07:42.816 --> 00:07:44.039
The name Thara is beautiful too.

00:07:49.385 --> 00:07:50.679
But besides just your name.

00:07:52.987 --> 00:07:54.783
I want to get to know you much better.

00:08:05.065 --> 00:08:06.081
Can you promise me.

00:08:07.198 --> 00:08:08.436
That once we leave this place.

00:08:09.785 --> 00:08:10.825
We'll still be friends.

00:08:24.653 --> 00:08:26.025
Do you really want us to be just friends?

00:11:09.124 --> 00:11:10.688
Despite the toughness of this training,

00:11:10.922 --> 00:11:12.952
You have all made it through with grace.

00:11:14.472 --> 00:11:15.536
I am very pleased.

00:11:16.585 --> 00:11:18.110
I am both happy and proud.

00:11:18.967 --> 00:11:19.971
To have female police officers,

00:11:20.543 --> 00:11:22.937
who are as capable and high-quality
as all of you, serving as a vital force.

00:11:27.328 --> 00:11:28.427
Another matter for today.

00:11:29.613 --> 00:11:30.478
We are honored

00:11:31.716 --> 00:11:34.368
By the presence of Police General
Phakphum Ratchanon.

00:11:36.244 --> 00:11:38.582
Deputy Commissioner
General of the Royal Thai Police,

00:11:39.505 --> 00:11:40.336
To give a speech.

00:11:41.105 --> 00:11:43.056
And to present certificates
to each and every one of you.

00:11:45.825 --> 00:11:46.662
All rise.

00:11:59.405 --> 00:12:00.999
Salute the commanding officer.

00:12:01.364 --> 00:12:02.057
Stand tall.

00:12:05.219 --> 00:12:05.867
Please be seated.

00:12:11.287 --> 00:12:12.158
First of all,

00:12:13.284 --> 00:12:15.716
I would like to congratulate all of you,

00:12:16.315 --> 00:12:17.251
on completing the training,

00:12:17.556 --> 00:12:18.928
and graduating today.

00:12:19.358 --> 00:12:21.681
V.I.P. protection,

00:12:22.404 --> 00:12:26.199
is not just about physical ability alone.

00:12:27.681 --> 00:12:29.183
But we must use our intellect,

00:12:30.315 --> 00:12:30.999
instinct,

00:12:32.825 --> 00:12:33.669
spirit,

00:12:35.313 --> 00:12:36.913
and your heart,

00:12:37.699 --> 00:12:38.777
alongside one another.

00:12:39.752 --> 00:12:40.712
I hope that

00:12:40.985 --> 00:12:43.272
you will never forget this training.

00:12:43.927 --> 00:12:44.830
And use what you've learned

00:12:45.153 --> 00:12:46.593
to protect people

00:12:47.044 --> 00:12:48.312
to the best of your abilities

00:12:48.985 --> 00:12:51.595
and with true professionalism.

00:13:05.248 --> 00:13:06.288
I would like

00:13:06.505 --> 00:13:08.999
to share a little something personal.

00:13:09.305 --> 00:13:09.930
Today,

00:13:10.626 --> 00:13:11.547
my daughter

00:13:12.745 --> 00:13:13.607
is here as well.

00:13:19.210 --> 00:13:21.130
Her code is 021.

00:13:26.223 --> 00:13:27.805
Phavika Ratchanon.

00:13:46.327 --> 00:13:47.577
If, during the training

00:13:47.681 --> 00:13:48.730
my daughter

00:13:50.345 --> 00:13:52.119
has done anything to cause you trouble,

00:13:53.790 --> 00:13:55.438
or made things difficult for you,

00:13:57.319 --> 00:13:59.186
I sincerely apologize for that.

00:14:01.305 --> 00:14:03.859
Today, I'll allow everyone
to complain about her.

00:14:04.469 --> 00:14:05.456
You can criticize her,

00:14:06.084 --> 00:14:07.047
but please, don't be too harsh.

00:14:25.236 --> 00:14:26.881
This Saturday is my daughter's birthday.

00:14:27.345 --> 00:14:28.368
We're having a small celebration.

00:14:29.648 --> 00:14:30.750
Please bring Looknam along.

00:14:30.887 --> 00:14:32.247
The kids can be friends.

00:14:33.278 --> 00:14:34.199
Looknam, please come, dear.

00:14:35.145 --> 00:14:36.830
You don't need to bring any gifts, dear.

00:14:37.361 --> 00:14:38.866
Just coming to play with her is enough.

00:14:39.850 --> 00:14:40.407
Yes.

00:14:41.020 --> 00:14:42.244
- Hello.
- Oh.

00:14:42.282 --> 00:14:43.103
Hello.

00:14:43.150 --> 00:14:44.445
- Hello. Hello.
- Hello.

00:14:45.444 --> 00:14:46.801
Happy birthday, little one.

00:14:47.174 --> 00:14:48.093
Thank you.

00:14:49.545 --> 00:14:51.690
Go leave the gift with your mom first.

00:14:51.737 --> 00:14:53.669
Then, take P'Looknam inside
to have some snacks.

00:14:53.699 --> 00:14:54.472
- Yes.
- Please.

00:14:56.385 --> 00:14:57.242
- Mom.
- Huh.

00:14:57.275 --> 00:15:00.128
P’Looknam brought me a gift
and so did the other friends.

00:15:00.211 --> 00:15:01.411
Ok.

00:15:01.826 --> 00:15:02.270
Wow.

00:15:05.636 --> 00:15:06.765
your name is Looknam?

00:15:06.952 --> 00:15:07.530
Yes.

00:15:07.767 --> 00:15:08.558
Hmm.

00:15:09.346 --> 00:15:09.885
Cute.

00:15:10.084 --> 00:15:11.672
The name really suits the owner.

00:15:12.105 --> 00:15:12.934
Thank you.

00:15:14.167 --> 00:15:14.970
See?

00:15:15.505 --> 00:15:17.622
Her name is quite Thai.

00:15:18.436 --> 00:15:19.162
It’s actually very cute.

00:15:20.469 --> 00:15:21.808
But Nong Noo sounds so old-fashioned.

00:15:21.862 --> 00:15:23.349
It's old-fashioned.

00:15:26.093 --> 00:15:27.266
Thank you for coming, dear.

00:15:27.376 --> 00:15:27.968
Yes.

00:15:28.475 --> 00:15:32.211
Happy birthday day to you

00:15:32.454 --> 00:15:35.776
Happy birthday day to you

00:15:36.063 --> 00:15:39.921
Happy birthday day, Happy birthday day.

00:15:39.956 --> 00:15:46.641
Happy birthday day to you

00:15:46.881 --> 00:15:47.509
Go ahead, blow it!

00:15:49.657 --> 00:15:50.510
Oh.

00:15:50.546 --> 00:15:52.865
Yay.

00:15:53.642 --> 00:15:55.035
Be a good girl for your mom, okay?

00:15:56.425 --> 00:15:57.906
I wish you so much happiness, dear.

00:16:02.025 --> 00:16:03.545
- So, shall we start opening the gifts now?
- Let's do it!

00:16:03.865 --> 00:16:04.235
Hurry up.

00:16:04.291 --> 00:16:09.867
- Open mine first, Open mine.
- Open mine.

00:16:09.897 --> 00:16:12.742
- Open mine.
- Open mine.

00:16:12.792 --> 00:16:13.559
This one.

00:16:15.592 --> 00:16:17.065
- Huh?
- Huh?

00:16:17.385 --> 00:16:18.531
A pencil case.

00:16:18.570 --> 00:16:20.783
- It’s as cute as you are.
- And it's pink, too.

00:16:21.162 --> 00:16:21.719
Do you like it?

00:16:22.007 --> 00:16:23.310
- I love it.
- Hmm.

00:16:23.399 --> 00:16:25.044
- Which one? Which one?
- This one is mine!

00:16:25.062 --> 00:16:26.030
Which one would you like, Nong Noo?

00:16:26.115 --> 00:16:27.456
- Take your pick.
- Let's go with this one first.

00:16:31.835 --> 00:16:32.330
Whoa!

00:16:32.650 --> 00:16:33.485
A storybook.

00:16:34.839 --> 00:16:36.267
An English storybook, too.

00:16:36.673 --> 00:16:38.727
The title is Frog and Toad.

00:16:43.505 --> 00:16:44.638
This one is mine.

00:16:44.682 --> 00:16:45.876
- Umm.
- Whoa.

00:16:46.220 --> 00:16:46.893
Do you like it?

00:16:47.145 --> 00:16:48.436
Yeah.

00:16:55.402 --> 00:16:57.749
Frog and Toad were best friends.

00:16:58.318 --> 00:16:59.103
One day...

00:16:59.601 --> 00:17:01.832
Toad was sitting in front of his house.

00:17:02.673 --> 00:17:04.199
He looked very sad.

00:17:05.056 --> 00:17:06.179
He said,

00:17:06.650 --> 00:17:07.681
No one

00:17:07.808 --> 00:17:10.211
has ever written him a letter.

00:17:10.389 --> 00:17:11.627
Frog heard this,

00:17:11.825 --> 00:17:13.225
so he rushed back home.

00:17:13.485 --> 00:17:16.051
He took out a piece of paper and wrote.

00:17:16.679 --> 00:17:17.705
Dear Toad,

00:17:18.145 --> 00:17:20.558
You are my very best friend.

00:17:20.985 --> 00:17:23.103
I am happy that you are in my life.

00:17:24.105 --> 00:17:25.017
After that,

00:17:25.307 --> 00:17:25.953
Frog

00:17:26.907 --> 00:17:28.747
Went to find the mail bird.

00:17:29.053 --> 00:17:30.217
and said,

00:17:31.645 --> 00:17:33.204
Please deliver this to Toad.

00:17:34.585 --> 00:17:36.466
I want to got a letter too.

00:17:37.841 --> 00:17:38.804
I'll send you one myself.

00:17:44.155 --> 00:17:45.376
Smile for the camera, dear!

00:17:51.346 --> 00:17:52.202
How was the training?

00:17:52.300 --> 00:17:53.266
It's quite tough, sir.

00:17:54.075 --> 00:17:54.934
And how about my daughter?

00:17:55.032 --> 00:17:55.959
She was great, sir.

00:17:56.377 --> 00:17:56.813
Sir.

00:17:57.159 --> 00:17:59.100
Thank you very much
for being here today, sir.

00:18:00.063 --> 00:18:00.623
Excuse me.

00:18:02.288 --> 00:18:03.073
Daddy.

00:18:07.915 --> 00:18:08.905
I miss you.

00:18:09.956 --> 00:18:10.967
How are you?

00:18:10.993 --> 00:18:11.850
How are you?

00:18:22.573 --> 00:18:23.402
How are you?

00:18:23.657 --> 00:18:24.211
Are you doing well?

00:18:24.537 --> 00:18:25.553
- Ok.
- Ok?

00:18:29.005 --> 00:18:29.965
What happened to your hand?

00:18:32.463 --> 00:18:33.592
Just a minor accident.

00:18:34.771 --> 00:18:35.533
But it’s nothing serious.

00:18:37.885 --> 00:18:38.626
An accident?

00:18:41.156 --> 00:18:42.288
This is a big deal.

00:18:42.848 --> 00:18:44.039
Why didn't you tell me.

00:18:45.065 --> 00:18:47.085
You and P’X are both the same.

00:18:47.370 --> 00:18:48.416
There have been so many times.

00:18:48.576 --> 00:18:49.752
That you've tricked me into coming here.

00:18:49.903 --> 00:18:51.287
I still haven't settled the score with you yet.

00:18:51.965 --> 00:18:52.318
Well...

00:18:52.653 --> 00:18:55.041
I didn't want you to worry,
so you could focus on your training.

00:18:55.444 --> 00:18:57.752
Look, I'm perfectly fine. I'm still very strong.

00:18:58.303 --> 00:18:59.168
Don't you know?

00:18:59.305 --> 00:19:00.798
Your dad is made of steel!

00:19:04.084 --> 00:19:04.430
Hm.

00:19:05.947 --> 00:19:06.667
Dad,

00:19:07.527 --> 00:19:08.712
I have someone

00:19:08.907 --> 00:19:10.119
I’d like to introduce to you.

00:19:10.839 --> 00:19:11.387
Who is it?

00:19:20.105 --> 00:19:22.567
Thank you so much for honoring
us with your presence today, sir.

00:19:23.316 --> 00:19:25.130
I’ve wanted to meet you
in person for a long time.

00:19:25.505 --> 00:19:27.675
021 I mean, Ms. Phavika.

00:19:27.782 --> 00:19:28.765
You are very impressive.

00:19:28.949 --> 00:19:31.684
I’ve known since the first day
that you were something special.

00:19:32.896 --> 00:19:34.647
The apple really doesn't fall far from the tree.

00:19:36.072 --> 00:19:37.844
In that case,

00:19:38.235 --> 00:19:39.604
let’s exchange Line contacts, shall we?

00:19:41.716 --> 00:19:42.513
Sure.

00:19:44.025 --> 00:19:46.327
May we please take a photo with you, sir?

00:19:46.505 --> 00:19:47.633
Sure thing, come on in!

00:19:49.509 --> 00:19:50.380
Please excuse me for a moment.

00:19:50.555 --> 00:19:52.170
I’ll go fetch my friends first.

00:19:53.876 --> 00:19:54.801
May I

00:19:57.047 --> 00:19:57.767
Oh, sure.

00:19:59.334 --> 00:20:00.368
Hello, Vicky.

00:20:01.150 --> 00:20:01.962
Congratulations!

00:20:11.192 --> 00:20:11.894
We...

00:20:12.383 --> 00:20:13.299
Do we know each other?

00:20:14.353 --> 00:20:15.139
I'm Bawornthat,

00:20:15.328 --> 00:20:16.703
Minister Burin's son.

00:20:17.118 --> 00:20:18.152
I used to have black hair,

00:20:18.505 --> 00:20:19.737
but I'm looking a bit too cool now,

00:20:19.956 --> 00:20:21.005
so it’s red.

00:20:27.745 --> 00:20:29.995
Ah, Minister Burin.

00:20:31.722 --> 00:20:32.528
Congratulations.

00:20:35.385 --> 00:20:36.570
How was your day? Are you tired?

00:20:38.152 --> 00:20:38.620
Well...

00:20:38.973 --> 00:20:39.903
It was quite tiring.

00:20:40.027 --> 00:20:41.136
Wow.

00:20:41.785 --> 00:20:44.306
My son just came back
from abroad earlier this year.

00:20:45.426 --> 00:20:47.796
I'd like him to get to know your daughter.

00:20:48.937 --> 00:20:50.445
If the two of them like each other.

00:20:50.715 --> 00:20:51.693
That would be wonderful.

00:20:57.103 --> 00:20:57.909
By the way.

00:20:58.345 --> 00:20:59.082
Do you like flowers?

00:20:59.118 --> 00:21:00.119
What exactly are you doing?

00:21:02.386 --> 00:21:03.873
Well, I’m just here for the party meeting.

00:21:06.336 --> 00:21:07.616
When my daughter opened her shop.

00:21:07.968 --> 00:21:09.225
You already meddled once.

00:21:10.457 --> 00:21:12.392
- And now, you’ve brought your son here yourself.
- Please excuse me.

00:21:13.127 --> 00:21:13.696
Umm.

00:21:14.705 --> 00:21:16.659
Don't be so cynical.

00:21:17.808 --> 00:21:19.876
I was just showing some kindness.

00:21:20.721 --> 00:21:21.556
I know

00:21:22.036 --> 00:21:23.316
you're threatening me.

00:21:23.865 --> 00:21:26.439
This is exactly why I suggested
that our families join together.

00:21:27.405 --> 00:21:28.727
If we were on the same side,

00:21:29.512 --> 00:21:31.411
I would have no reason to threaten you.

00:21:32.105 --> 00:21:35.257
I can’t be on the same side as
someone who tried to have me killed.

00:21:36.665 --> 00:21:39.965
But didn't we used to be on the same side?

00:21:40.350 --> 00:21:41.580
You know exactly why that changed.

00:21:42.688 --> 00:21:44.377
Stop using your old tactics.

00:21:45.684 --> 00:21:46.347
I know

00:21:46.833 --> 00:21:48.718
that the opposition is coming after you.

00:21:50.436 --> 00:21:51.862
If you don't want to end up in prison

00:21:52.093 --> 00:21:53.450
sooner than you should.

00:21:54.339 --> 00:21:55.533
Stay away from my daughter.

00:22:23.213 --> 00:22:24.312
I'm Vicky.

00:22:24.756 --> 00:22:26.315
My real name is Phavika.

00:22:27.331 --> 00:22:28.629
That's a very beautiful name.

00:22:36.419 --> 00:22:38.333
Her code is 021.

00:22:39.825 --> 00:22:41.402
Phavika Ratchanon.

00:23:26.066 --> 00:23:26.890
Hey, she's here.

00:23:27.705 --> 00:23:28.063
Wait.

00:23:28.484 --> 00:23:29.447
Why are you alone?

00:23:30.105 --> 00:23:30.528
Yeah.

00:23:32.857 --> 00:23:34.641
Wasn't 021 supposed to come back with us?

00:23:35.945 --> 00:23:36.771
She’s inside.

00:23:38.001 --> 00:23:39.168
I guess she's going back with her dad.

00:23:41.385 --> 00:23:41.906
Let's go.

00:23:52.993 --> 00:23:53.565
Tarn.

00:23:54.229 --> 00:23:54.922
- Tarn.
- Wait.

00:23:57.505 --> 00:23:58.128
What's wrong.

00:24:07.367 --> 00:24:07.856
Huh?

00:24:09.556 --> 00:24:11.527
Is 021 really Deputy
Commissioner Phakphum’s daughter?

00:24:14.134 --> 00:24:14.596
Wait.

00:24:15.865 --> 00:24:18.022
Are you two hiding something from me?

00:24:21.426 --> 00:24:22.214
Look, it's like this.

00:24:23.290 --> 00:24:25.041
Deputy Phakphum is the Deputy Chief of Police,

00:24:25.319 --> 00:24:27.097
and Tarn doesn't really get along with him.

00:24:27.505 --> 00:24:29.278
But somehow, she still wants to work for him.

00:24:30.004 --> 00:24:31.032
That's all I know.

00:24:33.470 --> 00:24:33.909
Tarn.

00:24:35.361 --> 00:24:36.063
What's going on?

00:24:36.496 --> 00:24:37.527
Talk to me.

00:24:46.226 --> 00:24:47.728
I’ve told you guys before, right?

00:24:49.239 --> 00:24:50.484
That my dad fell to his death.

00:24:56.596 --> 00:24:57.758
My mom and I believe

00:24:59.905 --> 00:25:01.225
that it wasn't a suicide.

00:25:02.830 --> 00:25:04.576
Why did you do this?

00:25:21.521 --> 00:25:25.201
- Sir, Mr. Wikarn fell and died at the scene.
- Who is going to take care of our child?

00:25:26.896 --> 00:25:27.660
We're processing

00:25:27.820 --> 00:25:30.377
evidence to find the cause, sir.

00:25:36.187 --> 00:25:37.198
Mrs.

00:25:37.479 --> 00:25:38.119
Mrs.

00:25:38.472 --> 00:25:40.750
please calm down. Stay calm.

00:25:41.545 --> 00:25:43.530
Phi.

00:25:47.859 --> 00:25:48.949
Twenty years ago,

00:25:49.936 --> 00:25:52.436
My father was threatened by a capitalist
to sell our shophouses at a cheap price.

00:25:54.318 --> 00:25:55.399
The villagers were terrified,

00:25:56.359 --> 00:25:57.414
so they all gave in and sold their places.

00:26:00.371 --> 00:26:01.379
But my father refused.

00:26:02.513 --> 00:26:04.582
He became the leader,
fighting back against that capitalist.

00:26:04.819 --> 00:26:06.333
He gathered all the evidence and went to the police.

00:26:10.979 --> 00:26:12.620
The officer in charge of the case back then

00:26:14.635 --> 00:26:16.075
was Inspector Phakphum Ratchanon.

00:26:20.985 --> 00:26:22.620
My father was in contact with him
for nearly a year.

00:26:25.745 --> 00:26:27.450
It seemed like he was on my father's side.

00:26:31.939 --> 00:26:33.802
But for some reason, my father ended up dead.

00:26:38.502 --> 00:26:39.248
Inspector, sir.

00:26:39.604 --> 00:26:42.084
Could you please tell me a bit
more about what happened that day?

00:26:42.807 --> 00:26:44.347
I went to see him at his house that day,

00:26:45.044 --> 00:26:47.213
around 3 PM.

00:26:47.811 --> 00:26:49.233
From our conversation,

00:26:50.164 --> 00:26:51.307
he seemed extremely stressed.

00:26:52.187 --> 00:26:54.967
He was talking in circles.
It didn't make much sense.

00:26:55.598 --> 00:26:56.816
Maybe... well,

00:26:57.622 --> 00:26:58.179
he was stressed.

00:26:58.534 --> 00:27:00.229
I could really feel how overwhelmed he was.

00:27:01.799 --> 00:27:02.540
And then what?

00:27:04.798 --> 00:27:06.208
He told me he couldn't take it anymore.

00:27:08.469 --> 00:27:09.663
He didn't want to fight anymore.

00:27:11.103 --> 00:27:12.087
He said if anything happened to him,

00:27:12.676 --> 00:27:13.773
to please look after his wife and child.

00:27:20.380 --> 00:27:22.712
The police concluded that
my father committed suicide.

00:27:25.201 --> 00:27:27.580
But no matter what, my mom refuses
to believe he would ever abandon us.

00:27:28.398 --> 00:27:29.725
My dad wasn't that kind of person

00:27:34.522 --> 00:27:36.670
One of the reasons
I became a cop was because of this.

00:27:39.062 --> 00:27:40.662
I want to know what really happened,

00:27:43.091 --> 00:27:45.174
and I've been waiting for the moment to face him.

00:27:46.599 --> 00:27:48.176
But it's freaking dangerous, Tarn.

00:27:49.746 --> 00:27:51.402
He’s risen so high now.

00:27:52.682 --> 00:27:53.894
There’s no way you can take him down.

00:27:56.593 --> 00:27:57.574
If I were your father,

00:28:00.105 --> 00:28:03.174
I wouldn't want you to
risk your life and your future.

00:28:05.025 --> 00:28:07.705
For a truth that might not even be provable.

00:28:14.359 --> 00:28:16.481
So you guys are just going
to leave me wondering like this?

00:28:20.065 --> 00:28:21.497
Even if I can't get revenge,

00:28:23.462 --> 00:28:24.463
I still need to know.

00:28:27.032 --> 00:28:28.836
But he's 021’s father!

00:28:29.444 --> 00:28:29.968
Umm.

00:28:31.530 --> 00:28:32.783
Now that you know this,

00:28:34.371 --> 00:28:35.939
does it make things harder

00:28:36.705 --> 00:28:37.675
or easier?

00:29:46.863 --> 00:29:47.930
Is she asleep?

00:29:48.955 --> 00:29:49.859
Or she is working?

00:30:00.745 --> 00:30:02.516
It seems like you
really like this friend of yours.

00:30:08.745 --> 00:30:10.333
She's a very kind person.

00:30:11.085 --> 00:30:13.192
And she's very gentle, too.

00:30:14.564 --> 00:30:15.746
But when something serious,

00:30:16.140 --> 00:30:17.447
she’s incredibly precise.

00:30:17.562 --> 00:30:18.765
Just like you, Dad.

00:30:20.265 --> 00:30:22.004
Sometimes, I even think.

00:30:22.291 --> 00:30:24.365
That she should be your child instead of me.

00:30:24.987 --> 00:30:25.891
Is that so?

00:30:26.715 --> 00:30:27.604
And what’s his name?

00:30:29.633 --> 00:30:30.739
Tara.

00:30:30.813 --> 00:30:31.707
Captain Tarn.

00:30:34.558 --> 00:30:37.142
She's the one who helped me
at the shop that day.

00:30:38.638 --> 00:30:39.657
It’s unbelievable.

00:30:39.992 --> 00:30:41.622
It's like fate is playing a joke on us.

00:30:42.179 --> 00:30:43.171
Crazy coincidence.

00:31:03.585 --> 00:31:04.288
Where are you going?

00:31:05.515 --> 00:31:06.561
Hanging out, Pa.

00:31:07.331 --> 00:31:08.374
Do you expect me to just wither away at home?

00:31:09.189 --> 00:31:10.522
Did you go see Phakphum's daughter yet?

00:31:11.817 --> 00:31:12.579
Already did, Pa.

00:31:12.999 --> 00:31:13.755
She’s not even that pretty.

00:31:14.422 --> 00:31:15.177
And she’s not really my type.

00:31:15.613 --> 00:31:16.377
Don't tell me.

00:31:16.967 --> 00:31:18.709
You prefer that old doctor lady.

00:31:19.731 --> 00:31:21.017
Women like the ones you prefer

00:31:22.158 --> 00:31:22.842
are hard to control.

00:31:23.444 --> 00:31:24.552
Find someone submissive.

00:31:24.919 --> 00:31:25.936
They're much easier to control.

00:31:28.374 --> 00:31:30.223
I don’t care who you sleep with.

00:31:30.884 --> 00:31:32.697
But if you can make Vicky fall for you,

00:31:33.278 --> 00:31:34.531
it’ll be to my advantage.

00:31:35.699 --> 00:31:36.448
You know very well

00:31:37.254 --> 00:31:38.813
that I’m in a tight spot right now.

00:31:39.345 --> 00:31:42.457
If that guy Phakphum leaks
the evidence to the opposition.

00:31:43.192 --> 00:31:44.072
We’re screwed.

00:31:45.376 --> 00:31:45.945
Pa.

00:31:46.625 --> 00:31:47.971
Just get rid of him, Pa.

00:31:48.454 --> 00:31:49.488
Like you did with the others.

00:31:50.545 --> 00:31:51.891
He won't be lucky enough
to survive every time.

00:31:56.632 --> 00:31:57.319
Thank you.

00:31:57.636 --> 00:31:58.454
Thank you.

00:32:03.124 --> 00:32:03.710
Hey, Pete.

00:32:04.072 --> 00:32:07.082
You have to stop Tarn from
working with that Deputy, you hear me?

00:32:07.832 --> 00:32:08.786
You've got to make it happen.

00:32:09.545 --> 00:32:10.238
You know what.

00:32:14.220 --> 00:32:15.266
Pete, I gotta go. Talk later!

00:32:17.346 --> 00:32:17.962
P'Ann.

00:32:19.505 --> 00:32:20.241
P'Ann.

00:32:21.364 --> 00:32:22.288
Are you alright?

00:32:24.102 --> 00:32:25.331
I’m just feeling a bit dizzy.

00:32:26.573 --> 00:32:27.660
I guess I haven’t had enough sleep.

00:32:28.762 --> 00:32:29.725
Are you sure you’re okay?

00:32:31.085 --> 00:32:31.971
Yeah, I'm good.

00:32:34.027 --> 00:32:35.479
Careful. Take a seat, slowly.

00:32:42.739 --> 00:32:45.121
Don’t get so caught up with
patients that you forget yourself.

00:32:46.976 --> 00:32:48.534
I've been clearing my schedule lately.

00:32:49.361 --> 00:32:51.536
I'm thinking of taking a break
and going abroad for a while.

00:32:52.842 --> 00:32:53.565
Hey.

00:32:54.395 --> 00:32:55.156
Or...

00:32:56.392 --> 00:32:58.297
Is there a surprise proposal?

00:32:59.402 --> 00:33:00.179
Don't be silly.

00:33:00.250 --> 00:33:01.316
I'm still very much single.

00:33:01.722 --> 00:33:02.110
Wait.

00:33:02.519 --> 00:33:03.011
Then...

00:33:03.577 --> 00:33:06.463
Who’s that guy?
The one with the glam look?

00:33:07.950 --> 00:33:09.382
You know,

00:33:09.533 --> 00:33:11.337
the one you went out to dinner with last week.

00:33:13.625 --> 00:33:14.247
Noey.

00:33:14.573 --> 00:33:15.927
Don't tell anyone about this yet.

00:33:16.273 --> 00:33:17.340
It’s not official yet.

00:33:20.913 --> 00:33:21.705
Got it!

00:33:43.284 --> 00:33:44.596
I have a favor to ask you.

00:33:45.574 --> 00:33:47.287
It won't interfere with your main duties.

00:33:49.429 --> 00:33:50.211
During your days off,

00:33:51.505 --> 00:33:53.767
I'd like you to help provide some security.

00:33:55.568 --> 00:33:56.564
No problem at all, sir.

00:33:58.030 --> 00:34:00.727
I haven't even told you yet
who you'll be looking after.

00:34:02.887 --> 00:34:03.841
Isn't it you, sir?

00:34:06.451 --> 00:34:07.287
It's my daughter.

00:34:07.968 --> 00:34:08.558
Vicky.

00:34:11.639 --> 00:34:13.950
Ever since that night,
I've been very worried about her.

00:34:14.905 --> 00:34:16.273
The reason I sent Vicky for training

00:34:16.599 --> 00:34:18.060
was so she could learn to defend herself.

00:34:19.702 --> 00:34:21.053
But if someone was there to look after her.

00:34:22.522 --> 00:34:23.909
I'd feel much better.

00:34:26.256 --> 00:34:27.882
She trusts you.

00:34:30.125 --> 00:34:31.245
And I trust you.

00:34:38.072 --> 00:34:39.310
I've received the package, P'Mart.

00:34:40.066 --> 00:34:40.472
Oh.

00:34:40.945 --> 00:34:43.358
It’s been changed to the meeting room
on the third floor?

00:34:44.865 --> 00:34:45.823
Which building?

00:34:51.749 --> 00:34:52.380
I see.

00:34:52.481 --> 00:34:53.719
Building Three.

00:35:01.370 --> 00:35:02.638
If I may speak frankly,

00:35:03.665 --> 00:35:05.826
I don't want to spend my off-time carrying bags

00:35:05.856 --> 00:35:08.007
for some high-society while she's shopping.

00:35:09.426 --> 00:35:11.251
I thought you knew my daughter well enough

00:35:11.622 --> 00:35:12.902
not to say something like that.

00:35:17.604 --> 00:35:18.196
Fine.

00:35:19.425 --> 00:35:20.804
I’ll take that as a refusal.

00:35:28.057 --> 00:35:29.133
Okay. I'll do it.

00:36:15.607 --> 00:36:16.469
Hey, stop.

00:36:18.466 --> 00:36:19.053
Hey.

00:36:34.945 --> 00:36:35.687
Mr. Bawornthat.

00:36:37.008 --> 00:36:37.725
Captain Tarn.

00:36:42.724 --> 00:36:44.356
I was just going to help Vicky carry her things.

00:36:46.045 --> 00:36:46.916
Do you two know each other?

00:36:51.065 --> 00:36:52.377
This is Mr. Bawornthat.

00:36:52.705 --> 00:36:54.507
Minister Burin’s son.

00:36:55.479 --> 00:36:56.187
And this

00:36:56.644 --> 00:36:57.779
Captain Tarn.

00:36:58.333 --> 00:36:59.008
A friend of mine

00:37:06.214 --> 00:37:08.004
Pleasure to meet you, Captain Tarn.

00:37:11.402 --> 00:37:12.033
Hello.

00:37:13.213 --> 00:37:14.516
I'm sorry, I misunderstood the situation.

00:37:16.739 --> 00:37:18.182
I happened to have a meeting nearby,

00:37:18.819 --> 00:37:20.454
so I thought I’d ask Vicky out for lunch.

00:37:22.395 --> 00:37:23.260
I’m afraid that’s not possible.

00:37:24.362 --> 00:37:25.127
It’s almost 1 PM already.

00:37:28.875 --> 00:37:29.832
She's right.

00:37:30.185 --> 00:37:31.485
I have another meeting soon,

00:37:31.521 --> 00:37:33.635
and I need to deliver these items
to my seniors.

00:37:33.796 --> 00:37:34.146
I see.

00:37:34.558 --> 00:37:35.257
That's fine.

00:37:35.918 --> 00:37:37.121
Maybe next time then.

00:37:37.980 --> 00:37:39.696
I hope I'll have the honor of your company, Vicky.

00:37:42.433 --> 00:37:43.473
And Captain Tarn.

00:37:45.838 --> 00:37:47.553
I'm sorry if I startled you earlier.

00:37:53.361 --> 00:37:55.260
We'll be taking our leave now.

00:37:56.119 --> 00:37:56.700
Let's go.

00:38:03.358 --> 00:38:04.196
Captain Tarn.

00:38:09.710 --> 00:38:11.142
Why haven’t you been answering my calls?

00:38:11.585 --> 00:38:13.912
I was actually planning to go
and wait for you at your office.

00:38:14.945 --> 00:38:15.817
I've been really busy with work.

00:38:17.992 --> 00:38:18.585
Still,

00:38:19.825 --> 00:38:20.949
don't overwork yourself.

00:38:21.622 --> 00:38:22.318
I'm worried.

00:38:23.912 --> 00:38:25.613
You're the one who’s more concerned.

00:38:26.305 --> 00:38:27.947
You're on the phone without
looking at your surroundings.

00:38:28.345 --> 00:38:30.270
What if someone with bad
intentions was actually following you?

00:38:32.745 --> 00:38:33.752
Hey, you...

00:38:34.105 --> 00:38:34.567
Hey!

00:38:51.313 --> 00:38:51.894
Ouch!

00:39:24.745 --> 00:39:26.765
Ever since that night at Vicky’s shop.

00:39:27.162 --> 00:39:28.149
I’ve been very worried about her.

00:39:28.739 --> 00:39:30.976
I’d like you to help provide some security

00:40:03.358 --> 00:40:05.281
I thought you said you were
going to stop seeing that rich girl.

00:40:08.545 --> 00:40:09.675
I've given it some thought.

00:40:10.750 --> 00:40:12.407
Being a bodyguard for anyone
is the same thing,

00:40:14.425 --> 00:40:16.697
As long as I can get into that house
to find evidence, that's enough.

00:40:17.693 --> 00:40:18.599
Don't be so stubborn.

00:40:19.482 --> 00:40:20.913
I know you too well, Tarn.

00:40:22.265 --> 00:40:23.174
You’re worried about her.

00:40:24.285 --> 00:40:26.300
I know what happened
at the Royal Thai Police HQ today.

00:40:27.402 --> 00:40:28.833
And I know exactly what you know,

00:40:29.435 --> 00:40:30.673
That this was likely no accident.

00:40:33.945 --> 00:40:35.790
If you're going because your heart tells you to,

00:40:36.493 --> 00:40:37.302
then I'm with you.

00:40:38.395 --> 00:40:40.576
But if you're going because
of Deputy Phakphum,

00:40:41.088 --> 00:40:42.196
then I’m against it.

00:40:43.761 --> 00:40:45.690
Because if Vicky ever finds out the truth,

00:40:46.705 --> 00:40:48.564
She’ll think you’ve just been using her as a tool.

00:40:52.490 --> 00:40:54.096
But I’ve had this in mind
since long before I knew her.

00:40:54.934 --> 00:40:56.353
She wasn't the reason I started this.

00:40:57.595 --> 00:40:59.684
And do you think she’ll understand that, Tarn?

00:41:00.505 --> 00:41:01.402
You have to make a choice.

00:41:02.113 --> 00:41:03.204
Whether you're going to keep investigating,

00:41:04.265 --> 00:41:05.287
Or choose Vicky,

00:41:05.488 --> 00:41:06.419
And just let the past go.

00:41:17.447 --> 00:41:19.210
Why does she have to be his daughter?

00:41:49.094 --> 00:41:50.193
So, this is Captain Tarn.

00:41:51.345 --> 00:41:51.945
Oh, wow.

00:41:52.585 --> 00:41:54.724
Who would've thought she’d be this beautiful?

00:41:56.119 --> 00:41:56.513
Huh?

00:41:57.225 --> 00:41:57.681
What?

00:41:59.100 --> 00:41:59.992
And who exactly is she protecting?

00:42:02.715 --> 00:42:03.139
Huh?

00:42:03.580 --> 00:42:04.256
Vicky?

00:42:18.005 --> 00:42:20.857
(All eyes on Bawornthat & Vicky: Political)

00:42:20.890 --> 00:42:24.004
(and Police heirs—the next power couple)

00:42:24.025 --> 00:42:24.857
Vicky.

00:42:34.065 --> 00:42:35.447
Who is Vicky?

00:42:36.478 --> 00:42:36.842
Oh.

00:42:37.835 --> 00:42:38.745
She is...

00:42:39.764 --> 00:42:41.025
Is...

00:42:41.340 --> 00:42:42.519
Are you talking business with a foreigner?

00:42:43.025 --> 00:42:43.530
Oh.

00:42:43.669 --> 00:42:44.810
Yeah, a foreign client

00:42:46.345 --> 00:42:48.060
You’re such a hard worker.

00:42:48.499 --> 00:42:49.494
You never stop working.

00:42:50.087 --> 00:42:50.910
So diligent.

00:42:51.915 --> 00:42:52.653
Come on,

00:42:53.032 --> 00:42:54.241
the folks in Europe are in a hurry.

00:42:55.056 --> 00:42:56.170
I miss you so much.

00:43:00.945 --> 00:43:02.860
Hold on, hold on.

00:43:03.133 --> 00:43:04.593
And about what you said

00:43:05.156 --> 00:43:06.356
taking me on a trip to Europe

00:43:07.145 --> 00:43:08.321
when should we go?

00:43:10.395 --> 00:43:10.899
Look,

00:43:11.476 --> 00:43:12.694
I'm really busy lately.

00:43:13.230 --> 00:43:14.312
Aren't you busy yourself?

00:43:19.118 --> 00:43:20.128
By the way,

00:43:20.505 --> 00:43:21.731
when did you reschedule
Deputy Phakphum’s surgery to?

00:43:22.285 --> 00:43:22.774
Hmm.

00:43:25.165 --> 00:43:26.356
I'm still looking for a date.

00:43:50.225 --> 00:43:51.263
Here comes.

00:43:51.838 --> 00:43:53.147
Here is the cake.

00:44:23.115 --> 00:44:23.950
Captain Tarn.

00:44:24.265 --> 00:44:25.124
Captain Tarn.

00:44:25.488 --> 00:44:26.762
It really is Captain Tarn.

00:44:26.946 --> 00:44:27.998
Wow.

00:44:28.345 --> 00:44:30.155
You’re so beautiful in person.

00:44:30.433 --> 00:44:31.020
stunning!

00:44:31.225 --> 00:44:32.152
Plus.

00:44:32.819 --> 00:44:33.829
You're so cool, too.

00:44:34.359 --> 00:44:35.693
I’m not dreaming, am I?

00:44:35.909 --> 00:44:37.159
Vicky, please tell me I'm not.

00:44:38.054 --> 00:44:38.466
Uh...

00:44:41.639 --> 00:44:42.164
Uh...

00:44:42.465 --> 00:44:44.297
I mean, I’m such a huge fan of yours,

00:44:44.570 --> 00:44:46.232
May I take a photo with you?

00:44:47.059 --> 00:44:47.995
Please?

00:44:48.374 --> 00:44:48.863
Sure.

00:44:49.974 --> 00:44:50.736
Thank you.

00:44:51.067 --> 00:44:52.030
A selfie is fine too.

00:44:54.099 --> 00:44:55.257
One, two, three.

00:44:56.054 --> 00:44:57.002
One, two, three.

00:44:58.306 --> 00:44:59.070
Thank you.

00:44:59.562 --> 00:45:00.570
Let me see the photo for sec.

00:45:01.965 --> 00:45:03.465
No, no, it's not very good.

00:45:03.820 --> 00:45:05.592
Um, Vicky, could you take a photo for me?

00:45:05.891 --> 00:45:07.349
Make it a good one, okay?

00:45:09.065 --> 00:45:10.196
Please.

00:45:13.265 --> 00:45:13.749
Fine.

00:45:14.078 --> 00:45:14.822
Thank you.

00:45:15.316 --> 00:45:15.947
Uh...

00:45:16.439 --> 00:45:17.530
A normal pose is fine.

00:45:19.225 --> 00:45:20.670
One, two, three.

00:45:21.260 --> 00:45:23.174
One, two, three.

00:45:24.330 --> 00:45:25.793
Oh, can we do a heart pose too?

00:45:26.839 --> 00:45:28.232
- Heart?
- Yes.

00:45:29.355 --> 00:45:29.945
Yes.

00:45:32.451 --> 00:45:33.998
One, two, three.

00:45:34.650 --> 00:45:35.894
- Here.
- Thank you.

00:45:38.253 --> 00:45:39.204
Wow.

00:45:39.802 --> 00:45:41.174
The photos are so beautiful!

00:45:41.773 --> 00:45:43.761
I can finally rest in peace tonight.

00:45:46.531 --> 00:45:47.275
Mali.

00:45:47.598 --> 00:45:49.299
She is a huge fan of the Captain.

00:45:50.225 --> 00:45:53.047
I guess it's time
to change your phone's wallpaper.

00:45:58.798 --> 00:45:59.385
Let's go.

00:46:00.433 --> 00:46:00.878
Uh...

00:46:01.459 --> 00:46:02.223
Wait a moment.

00:46:02.552 --> 00:46:03.168
Uh.

00:46:03.665 --> 00:46:07.284
Did you say you didn't know Captain Tarn?

00:46:07.505 --> 00:46:09.420
Why are you two together today?

00:46:18.507 --> 00:46:19.509
Uh.

00:46:19.785 --> 00:46:20.356
Well...

00:46:21.524 --> 00:46:22.756
We met during the training.

00:46:24.164 --> 00:46:26.063
Now we are...

00:46:31.429 --> 00:46:32.182
Friend.

00:46:34.297 --> 00:46:35.396
It’s because of my dad.

00:46:36.087 --> 00:46:37.654
After what happened at the shop last time,

00:46:37.743 --> 00:46:38.964
He’s been incredibly worried about me.

00:46:39.322 --> 00:46:41.328
So he assigned the Captain to look after me,

00:46:41.968 --> 00:46:42.851
Just for peace of mind.

00:46:44.611 --> 00:46:46.066
I feel safe now, too!

00:46:46.531 --> 00:46:48.054
Captain Tarn, you can come here every day.

00:46:48.465 --> 00:46:50.347
Even on the days Vicky doesn't come.

00:46:50.608 --> 00:46:52.116
You can still come by.

00:46:54.442 --> 00:46:55.583
I’d just be in the way.

00:46:55.776 --> 00:46:57.287
I'm not sure how much help I’d be.

00:46:57.530 --> 00:46:58.777
Not at all!

00:46:59.065 --> 00:47:00.961
Just standing there looking cool like this

00:47:01.162 --> 00:47:03.153
makes the customers feel safe.

00:47:05.248 --> 00:47:06.958
Take it down.

00:47:11.725 --> 00:47:15.467
Won't there be trouble having
the famous Captain Tarn as my subordinate?

00:47:16.768 --> 00:47:18.330
I’m more afraid that
I’ll be the one to mess things up.

00:47:19.417 --> 00:47:22.697
If you mess anything up,
I’m reporting you to the Department!

00:47:29.385 --> 00:47:30.330
Take off your shirt.

00:47:36.389 --> 00:47:37.213
Take it off.

00:47:37.865 --> 00:47:38.979
To bake.

00:47:39.494 --> 00:47:40.762
Weren't you going to help me?

00:47:42.842 --> 00:47:43.376
Oh.

00:47:44.564 --> 00:47:45.162
Yes.

00:47:55.195 --> 00:47:55.799
Over there.

00:47:56.027 --> 00:47:56.967
Put on your apron.

00:48:17.536 --> 00:48:18.413
Turn around.

00:48:50.110 --> 00:48:51.168
Captain Tarn...

00:48:51.980 --> 00:48:52.964
You actually have a pretty great figure.

00:49:01.073 --> 00:49:01.924
In this look...

00:49:03.571 --> 00:49:04.922
You're so cute it hurts.

00:49:10.567 --> 00:49:11.547
Silly girl.

00:49:26.247 --> 00:49:26.691
Oh.

00:49:28.016 --> 00:49:29.121
So, is there anything I can help you with?

00:49:30.905 --> 00:49:32.176
I should fold these boxes, right?

00:49:54.170 --> 00:49:55.482
I told you not to stare.

00:50:09.562 --> 00:50:10.466
But I want to.

00:50:11.056 --> 00:50:11.873
What are you gonna do about it?

00:50:53.847 --> 00:50:56.845
A good police must be
an enemy of bad people.

00:50:58.036 --> 00:51:00.327
If you're a bad cop,
you're an enemy of good people.

00:51:03.838 --> 00:51:05.779
I thought you said you
were done with that young lady.

00:51:09.865 --> 00:51:11.939
The statute of limitations for that
case will expire in a few months.

00:51:12.999 --> 00:51:14.217
If I let it slide,

00:51:14.993 --> 00:51:17.287
Burin won't have
to take any responsibility at all?

00:51:18.004 --> 00:51:18.967
I heard...

00:51:19.891 --> 00:51:22.173
You’ve become a bodyguard for Vicky?